ed out on a medal in Monday night's team final at the Bercy Arena, finishing fourth for the third Games in a row.\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 569, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 423, \"end\": 436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999864448555074, \"rank\": 1.3555197294146579e-05, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 466, \"to\": 473}, {\"ngram\": \"Monday night's team\", \"from\": 477, \"to\": 496}, {\"ngram\": \"the Bercy Arena\", \"from\": 506, \"to\": 521}, {\"ngram\": \"the third Games\", \"from\": 544, \"to\": 559}, {\"ngram\": \"a row\", \"from\": 563, \"to\": 568}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whitlock, who was part of the quintet that claimed an historic bronze at London 2012, had been seeking to win the seventh medal of his career, which would have moved him level with Sir Chris Hoy as the country's third-most decorated Olympian.\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 813, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 644, \"end\": 655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.562218129263559e-13, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 756, \"end\": 765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chris Hoy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\"}, {\"begin\": 804, \"end\": 812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999818310245, \"rank\": 1.8168895435415998e-08, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Whitlock\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 579}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 589, \"to\": 593}, {\"ngram\": \"the quintet\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 608}, {\"ngram\": \"an historic bronze\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 640}, {\"ngram\": \"the seventh medal\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 698}, {\"ngram\": \"his career\", \"from\": 702, \"to\": 712}, {\"ngram\": \"level\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 746}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, however, Britain were denied by an inspired American team as Japan snatched gold ahead of China in a dramatic finish.\", \"from\": 815, \"to\": 941, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 833, \"end\": 840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7664022091753336, \"rank\": 0.30479757140887875, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 868, \"end\": 876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998469489943362, \"rank\": 0.00015277523865264516, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 885, \"end\": 890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6918917082587773, \"rank\": 0.44525691165637, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 914, \"end\": 919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9777368953703861, \"rank\": 0.022761283576462125, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"